textBeforeTable: 2013-14 Women's Track & Field Personal: Daughter of Jeff Klein and Karen Dyer... One of six children, has two brothers (Al and Jeremy) and three sisters (Kendra, Virginia and Natalia)... Plans to major in psychology. Prep: Competed for Tim Taylor and Earl Lavender at David Lipscomb High School... 2009 state champion... Part of 2008 region championship team... Owns school's 5K cross country record. 2010 Cross Country: Picked up two top-20 finishes in five races as a freshman... Was 12th at the Louisville Invitational, running the 5K race in 19:43... Set a personal-best in the 5K with an 18:57.34 run at the Evansville Invitational. 2011 Track and Field: Earned personal-best 2:34.87s mark in the 800m run at the Shamrock Invitational, finishing 51st... Set personal-best in the 1500m run the following week at the Vanderbilt Black and Gold, finishing 17th with a 5:02.71s run... Finished 10th in the 1500m at the Governors Invitational (5:22.33s). 2012 Track and Field: Placed 12th in the mile run at the Niswonger Foundation Invitational with a personal-best time of 5:31.10s... Broke her personal best time in the 5000m finishing in 19:38.16s at the Ole Miss Invite. 2013 Track and Field: Finished 11th at the BSC 'Southern Invitational in the 1500m crossing the line in 5:07.36s... Set a personal best in the 800m at the Vanderbilt Black and Gold Invite crossing the line in 2:25.78s... Set a season best in the 1500m with a time of 5:06.00s
